05/10/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police have busted an international drug and arms smuggling ring, local media reported on Monday (October 4th). Seven Croatian citizens were arrested in the operation, conducted on Sunday. They are suspected of trafficking weapons from Bosnia and Herzegovina to Germany and The Netherlands, via Croatia. They are allegedly also involved in smuggling drugs from EU countries to Croatia. (HINA, javno.hr, Radio Free Europe - 04/10/10)
